PetOS Design System (Styleguide)

Visual Language: Luxe Tech / Industrial / Bauhaus influence.
Mood: Professional, Calm, Premium, Dark.

1. Color Palette

Base (Dark Mode)

Background: #121212 (Main), #1A1A1A (Cards/Surface).

Borders: neutral-800 (Subtle), neutral-700 (Active).

Text: white (Headings), neutral-400 (Body/Secondary).

Accents (Functional)

Rose Gold (Health/Urgent): Tailwind rose-500 / rose-400.

Use: Alerts, Medical info, Heart icon.

Neon Lime (Activity/Walks): Tailwind lime-400 / lime-500.

Use: Action buttons, Progress bars, Success states.

Amber (Warning/Gamification): Tailwind amber-400 / amber-500.

Use: Trophies, AI interaction, Attention needed.

Electric Blue (Travel): Tailwind blue-500 / blue-400.

Use: Flights, Documents, Information.

2. Typography

Font Family: Sans-serif (System default or Inter).

Headings: Bold, Tight tracking.

Labels: Uppercase, wide tracking, small size (text-[10px], tracking-wider).

Numbers: Monospaced for timers and weights (font-mono).

3. Components

Card (The Building Block)

<div className="bg-[#1A1A1A] border border-neutral-800 rounded-2xl p-4 shadow-lg">
  {/* Content */}
</div>


Quick Action Button (Circle)

Size: w-14 h-14

Shape: rounded-full

Interaction: active:scale-95

Shadow: shadow-lg shadow-[color]/20

Input Fields

Background: bg-neutral-900

Border: border-neutral-700

Focus: focus:border-[AccentColor]

Radius: rounded-xl or rounded-2xl

4. Effects

Glassmorphism: bg-black/60 backdrop-blur-md (For Modals/Bottom Sheets).

Gradients: Subtle linear gradients from-neutral-800 to-neutral-900 for depth.

Animation: transition-all duration-300 for all interactive elements.
